The Nigerian government, late Friday, recorded 11 new cases of the Covid-19 pandemic, bringing the total number to 81 in the country. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) posted on its official Twitter handle (@ncdcgov) that: “11 new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 8 in Lagos, 2 in Enugu & 1 in Edo State. “As at 11:55pm 27th March, there are 81 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. 3 have been discharged with 1 death.”  Before now, Enugu was COVID-19 free. The breakdown indicated that Lagos State is the most hit with 52 persons having the virus while the Federal Capital Territory is second with 14 confirmed cases. Ogun and Oyo has three each as Enugu, Edo and Bauchi are with two cases each. Rivers Osun and Ekiti has a case each. As at now, the virus is in 10 Nigerian states as 27 others have not recorded any case.  States are already making effort to limit the spread of the novel coronavirus and have ordered a complete lockdown.   Nigeria records five new coronavirus cases Oshiomhole tests negative to covid-19 Coronavirus: Nigeria’s confirmed cases rise to 40